A stunning coastal property in Cornwall has gone on the market for £2 million  and it comes with incredible sea views and a clifftop garden. The home is located directly above Perran Sands in Perranporth and enjoys unparalleled views across the beach and far out to sea. The home has four-bedrooms and three-bathroom and is decorated in light and bright tones. Across the home there are large windows that take full advantage of the panoramic views. On the ground floor is an entrance hall, dining room and sitting room, which features a wood-burning stove. In addition, there is a stunning kitchen with a door to the terrace, two double bedrooms and a family shower room. On the first floor sits the guest bedroom with an en suite bathroom, and a further bedroom suite with a dressing room. Outside, there is a beautiful clifftop garden that features a full width paved sun terrace and steps down to the lower lawned garden with rockery, flowerbeds and picket fence boundary. There is also a gravelled parking area for numerous vehicles, a timber clad garage and a private paved courtyard. The property is currently on sale for offers over £2,000,000 with Lillicrap Chilcott. Do you have a story to share? Get in touch by emailing MetroLifestyleTeam@Metro.co.uk. MORE : Couple halve their living costs by ditching renting to live in a van MORE : DIY mum transforms ‘boring’ bathroom in one day for just £28 MORE : Take a look inside a two-bedroom house on the market for just £5,000